## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- Use strict type checking
- Define interfaces for all data structures
- Use `type` for object shapes, `interface` for extendable types
- Avoid `any` type - use `unknown` when type is truly unknown

### React Components
- Use functional components with hooks
- Use `'use client'` directive for client components
- Follow Atomic Design pattern for components
- Use `forwardRef` for components that need ref forwarding
- Destructure props in component signature

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `LecturerTable.tsx`)
- Functions: camelCase (e.g., `handleFileSelect`)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for global, camelCase for local
- Files: Match the primary export name
- CSS classes: Use Tailwind utility classes

### Convex
- Define all tables in `schema.ts`
- Use indexes for frequently queried fields
- Keep functions focused on single responsibility
- Use `v.id('table')` for document references
- Handle errors with descriptive messages

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Use CSS variables for theming (defined in globals.css)
- Use `cn()` utility for conditional class merging
- Follow mobile-first responsive design
- Maintain consistent spacing using Tailwind's spacing scale

### File Organization
- One component per file
- Export components as named exports
- Keep files under 300 lines
- Group related functionality in directories

## Database Schema

### lecturers
- `name`: string - Lecturer's full name
- `nip`: string - Indonesian employee ID (unique)
- `expertise`: string[] - Areas of expertise
- `status`: string - active | on leave | inactive

### staff
- `name`: string - Staff member's name
- `nip`: string - Indonesian employee ID
- `role`: "Admin" | "Kaprodi" (Head of Department)

### teaching_schedules
- `lecturerId`: Id<'lecturers'> - Reference to lecturer
- `day`: string - Day of the week
- `startTime`: string - Start time (HH:MM)
- `endTime`: string - End time (HH:MM)
- `activity`: string - Activity description
- `room`: string (optional) - Room/location
- `notes`: string (optional) - Additional notes

### expertise_categories
- `fieldName`: string - Name of expertise area
- `description`: string (optional) - Description

## API Conventions

### Convex Functions
- `get`: Fetch single document by ID
- `getAll`: Fetch all documents
- `create`: Create new document
- `update`: Update existing document
- `remove`: Delete document
- `search`: Search with filters
- `bulkInsert`: Insert multiple documents

### CSV Upload
Required columns: NIP, Day, StartTime, EndTime, Activity
Optional columns: Room, Notes
- NIP must match an existing lecturer
- Time format: HH:MM (24-hour)
- Day: English or Indonesian day names

## Error Handling
- Use descriptive error messages
- Handle errors at component level
- Display user-friendly error messages
- Log errors for debugging (not in production)

## Testing Guidelines
- Test components in isolation
- Mock Convex functions for unit tests
- Test CSV parsing with various inputs
- Test responsive layouts at different viewports

## Git Commit Convention
- `feat:` New feature
- `fix:` Bug fix
- `refactor:` Code refactoring
- `style:` Styling changes
- `docs:` Documentation
- `test:` Testing
- `chore:` Maintenance tasks

## Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Provide ARIA labels for interactive elements
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain sufficient color contrast
- Support screen readers
